using an 8 GB heap for a **one-time migration** is completely reasonable.

---

# Final Summary

✅ Heap stores JavaScript objects.

✅ Heap Limit is only the maximum allowed memory.

✅ Node does NOT reserve 8 GB on startup.

✅ `toArray()` loads the entire collection into memory.

✅ Large collections can easily fill the heap.

✅ Increasing heap size is a temporary fix.

✅ Batch processing or cursors are the permanent solution.

✅ An 8 GB heap is safe on our 16 GB VPS for migration tasks.
